  <!-- NY Workers' Comp Requirements -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">New York Workers' Compensation Requirements</h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600">
          What Rochester employers need to know
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 max-w-5xl mx-auto">
        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">When It's Required</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-600">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-navy-600 mt-0.5 mr-2 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
              </svg>
              <span><strong>1 or more employees</strong> in NY (including part-time)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-navy-600 mt-0.5 mr-2 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
              </svg>
              <span>Sole proprietors and partners must carry coverage if they employ others</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-navy-600 mt-0.5 mr-2 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
              </svg>
              <span>Required for Rochester construction contractors, even with just one employee</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-navy-600 mt-0.5 mr-2 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
              </svg>
              <span>Coverage required from day one—before the first employee starts work</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Penalties for Non-Compliance</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-600">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-red-600 mt-0.5 mr-2 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z"></path>
              </svg>
              <span><strong>Fines up to $2,000</strong> per 10-day period without coverage</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-red-600 mt-0.5 mr-2 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z"></path>
              </svg>
              <span>Immediate <strong>stop-work orders</strong></span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-red-600 mt-0.5 mr-2 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z"></path>
              </svg>
              <span>Personal liability for all medical costs and lost wages</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-red-600 mt-0.5 mr-2 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z"></path>
              </svg>
              <span>Potential <strong>criminal charges</strong> for willful non-compliance</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-400 p-6 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          <strong>Rochester Business Tip:</strong> The NY Workers' Compensation Board actively monitors compliance. Don't risk your business—get covered today. We can provide same-day certificates for urgent needs.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Local FAQ -->
  <section class="py-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Rochester Workers' Comp Questions</h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600">
          Common questions from Western New York employers
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <details class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg p-6 cursor-pointer hover:shadow-xl transition-shadow duration-200">
          <summary class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 cursor-pointer">
            How much does workers' comp cost for Rochester businesses?
          </summary>
          <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            For Rochester employers, workers' comp costs typically range from <strong>$1-$2 per $100 of payroll</strong> for low-risk businesses (offices, tech companies) to <strong>$5-$15 per $100</strong> for high-risk industries (construction, manufacturing). Your exact rate depends on your industry classification, payroll, and claims history. Rochester-specific factors like winter weather-related claims can also impact rates for outdoor workers.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg p-6 cursor-pointer hover:shadow-xl transition-shadow duration-200">
          <summary class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 cursor-pointer">
            Do I need workers' comp for seasonal employees in Rochester?
          </summary>
          <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            Yes. In New York, <strong>all employees must be covered</strong> from their first day of work, including seasonal, part-time, and temporary workers. This is especially important for Rochester businesses that hire seasonal staff for winter operations (snow removal, holiday retail) or summer work (construction, festivals).
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg p-6 cursor-pointer hover:shadow-xl transition-shadow duration-200">
          <summary class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 cursor-pointer">
            Are lake-effect weather injuries covered?
          </summary>
          <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            Yes. Workers' compensation covers injuries from <strong>slips on ice, snow removal accidents, and weather-related incidents</strong> during work. Given Rochester's lake-effect snow (averaging 100+ inches), it's crucial your policy properly classifies outdoor workers and snow removal operations to ensure adequate coverage.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg p-6 cursor-pointer hover:shadow-xl transition-shadow duration-200">
          <summary class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 cursor-pointer">
            Can University of Rochester students be covered as employees?
          </summary>
          <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            If UR students work for your business as <strong>W-2 employees</strong> (not independent study or unpaid internships), they must be covered under your workers' compensation policy. This applies to part-time student workers, co-op students, and any other employees, regardless of their student status.
          </p>
        </details>

        <details class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg p-6 cursor-pointer hover:shadow-xl transition-shadow duration-200">
          <summary class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 cursor-pointer">
            How quickly can I get a certificate of insurance?
          </summary>
          <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            PCFG Insurance can often provide <strong>same-day certificates of insurance</strong> for Rochester businesses. This is critical when you need proof of coverage for contracts, construction permits, or vendor requirements. We understand Western NY businesses need fast service—contact us by 2 PM for same-day issuance.
          </p>
        </details>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 text-center">
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">Ready to protect your Rochester business?</p>
        <a href="#quote-form" class="inline-block bg-navy-600 hover:bg-navy-700 text-white px-8 py-3 rounded-md font-semibold transition-colors duration-200">
          Get Your Free Rochester Quote
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

